			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2703640">
									

<p>I, on the other hand, have always hated incomprehensibility. Obfuscating your story with tons of gibberish is a really great way to make me dislike your story.</p>
<p>The problem with writing stories that emulate dreams is that dreams don't have narrative cohesion. They're random mish-mashes of images with no logic or consistency behind them. And while that may be interesting, it doesn't make a good story.</p>

