			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2703621">
									

<p>There's something about Oneiroi articles that I find almost seductive. The way it's presented is so far deviated from the standard go-around here, and the subject matter is almost alien. It's very easy to find yourself engrossed in the story, and still unsure of what you experienced when it's over.</p>
<p>I don't feel like an Oneiroi article is acceptable, to me, without that feeling. The sense of drifting and uncertainty. Of something and someplace that is, and very much isn't.</p>
<p>Fortunately, this hits all of those points. A delightful read.</p>

