			<div class="content" id="post-content-2703630">
									

<p>After the MTF contest, I wondered if <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/xiupania">#Xiupania</a> was a lightning-strike sort of article, something that works fantastically once but then fails a bit when future articles use the same format. However, I'm happy to say that this document is a pretty sweet piece of work &#8212; it's all that classic Oneiroi dream logic that combines numbers stations, conspiracy theories, and ARGs to create something that feels very right.</p>
<p>If I could select an issue, I would say that it might have been even better to include formats that had not already been seen in #Xiupania. At the very least, I would encourage that for other people seeking to make articles in this format: let's not allow something so fresh and weird to become stale by reusing the same code snippets in everything.</p>
<p>Other than that, though, this is solid.</p>

